Today's session invites you to put the pieces together, dig into your tool bag and explore the unknown. 

Tap into your deep soulful breath today as this swift practice is designed to zip you out of your comfort zone. 

Go forth, be fierce, observe!

Meet and greet it with your inner smile. 

Direct your focus on what you want to manifest, not what you fear. Manifest what serves!

This is my 4th 30 days with Adriene and I love every single minute I spend on my mat listening to adrien. You are inspiring and are truly helping me live a better life. I sincerely mean that !!

However, lately I’ve been struggling to get to the mat. 8 days since my last practice and before that I’ve struggled to string more than 3 or 4 consecutive days. It’s so strange that something I know I love and I know makes me feel better and some how I still choose to watch tv or YouTube rather than take 20-30 mins first to do my yoga... 

Anyway, random inner struggles story I guess hehe 

My plan is to re commit to myself and to what makes me happier. Yoga is definitely one of those things!

Cheers everyone.

Oh my... when you started to guide us towards crow pose, my automatic response was no, not even going to try because I’m so weak, I never even get close to be able to lift my toes, why bother . But I’ve been actively working in my self esteem lately and told myself: it’s called practice, you don’t have to make it perfect, you just have to try and one day, if you keep practicing, you might do it, but the pose is not the point. Focus on sensation. And I did. AND F* DID IT!! I WAS ABLE TO LIFT MYSELF UP!! I couldn’t believe it. I even started crying, so often we limit ourselves with our thoughts. Thank you Adrienne for showing us to let them go ❤️

I do yoga in an EXTREMELY small space. Like, my mat takes up my ENTIRE floor, and almost doesn't fit. Also, the "Top" of my mat is actually the middle, since I have a loft bed and going to the top of my mat would end in a concussion. So, things like Warrior 3 are DIFFICULT. I spend so much time over analyzing just fitting my body in space that, in speedier practices like the one, by the time I've figured it out Adriene has moved three steps on. But I don't care. I make it work because I love yoga. Was today my most successful lesson? No. Did I still enjoy it?

I've been taking this challenge at the fastest pace I can over the past couple months and have been so grateful for these last couple practices especially as the world faces the coronavirus epidemic. I've had a lot of anxiety about the virus, school, and other personal challenges but today's practice let me get completely out of my head and challenged me when I wasn't expecting it. This was probably the most cathartic practice yet for me so thank you so much!

I did this practice today as we face a global pandemic and it was hard to show up on the mat. My balance was off, I felt heavy moving on the mat as I grieve for lost time at school for my little one, and lost income for myself. I am fortunate in so many ways in this crisis we find ourselves in and the fact that I made it through this practice, falling over, getting myself back up, and getting all the way through to the end is a testament to how we will make it through this current situation. Some days the movement comes easy, even in the challenging poses, today IT. WAS. HARD. But I committed to wellness and breath and made it through. Thank you as always Adriene. Every practice I learn something that my heart or body or soul is yearning for. Blessed Be.

This yoga practice, which I was going to swap for a shorter one because of fatigue but DIDN'T (!!) has me feeling fearless for my job tomorrow. Today I noticed some garbage, mostly cotton swabs (very random) in one of the ponds at work (I work at an outdoor summer camp). I felt awkward  and very self conscious for some reason going up to the maintenance worker and asking him for this pool cleaner like device ( a net) for me to fish out the cotton swabs. I really wanted to clean up the pond and specifically get those cotton swabs out of the pond because there are turtles in there! Just like the straw movement I have heard that cotton swabs are also a harmful shape for the turtles if they come into contact with them. ANYWAY, tomorrow I will ask my maintenance co-worker for his net so I can potentially help the turtles in the pond. BE FEARLESS. <3 Thank you Adriene, Namaste <3

Hi Adriene, I just wanted to take a moment to thank you so much for what you're doing. To be honest, the "True" sequence this year came at the perfect time for me, and I don't think I'd have been able to make it through this month without it. On January 11th, my Momma passed away from COPD/emphysema. I sat with her as she passed and watched the monitors show her brain activity for minutes after her lungs and hearts stopped. It solidified for me what I always inherently knew to be true, that our minds and bodies are two separate entities. The week after she passed, it was hard for me to take the time for yoga practice, and I fell a week behind. I finally got the nerve to get back to it, and one day did 3 practices because it just felt like what my body needed. Your commentary about self-love and taking the time to focus on our physical bodies and that connection has never come at a better time. It's helped solidify for me that my body is just a vessel, and I need to treat it with love and care, regardless of the other circumstances in my life. It's made me more aware of that connection and given me even more reassurance that I'll see my Momma in the spiritual world one day. I'm proud to say that I've caught up and will be finishing out the next two days of the journey with you guys. Again, thank you. Thank you, thank you, thank you. With everything I've been through, you've changed my life, and now yoga is finally a permanent fixture in my daily routine. Lots of love, Amber

I was definitely off balance today but I love this practice! Even if I couldn't hold warrior 3 for very long, I just tried my best and moved on with ease. It's amazing how transformative yoga can be for your mind and the way you view yourself. At the beginning of this journey, I was guilty of pushing myself into poses for the sake of getting there. Now I truly find what feels good and if I fall or lose my balance along the way, no worries 😊

My focus was to manifest power and courage not only within myself but for all human beings on the planet. I've been "putting the pieces together" for long enough to see exactly what's going on and once the veil (or denial) is lifted, my friends, it really does take a kick ass mama to be absolutely fearless. This is when you realize that THE MOST important thing to do is to love yourself, love others and roll out the mat each day to heal the body, the soul ... and the world! Adriene, you brought out the Warrior Spirit big time today. I stand with you all the way. Big Love to everyone here, Namaste!
